{
  "text": "The Nigerian Government could deploy this framework at all levels of government (e.g. national site prioritisation, regional management, or local site assessment) to address stakeholder concerns about participation in the land contamination management process (Rim-rukeh, 2015; UNEP, 2011). The framework could be used to facilitate workshops [CITATION_1] , or guide site investigations that require inclusion of different stakeholder groups [CITATION_2] , and also to determine remediation action (UNEP, 2011). By doing so, the outcome of the engagement process will reflect stakeholder expectations and might reduce the conflict that exists between land contamination stakeholders [CITATION_3] UNEP, 2011) .",
  "correct_citation": {
